President Obama released a statement on the death of Benjamin Bradlee, recognizing him as a journalist who believed in the importance of journalism for democracy. Bradlee, as the editor of the Washington Post, led a team of reporters who published the Pentagon Papers and exposed the Watergate scandal. President Obama praised Bradlee for setting a high standard for honest and objective reporting, which inspired many others to enter the profession. The President also mentioned that he honored Bradlee with the Presidential Medal of Freedom in 2013. Finally, he offered condolences to Bradlee's family and those who were fortunate to know him.